│ My last fix was too restrictive and caused numerous test failures. The issue is that completely disallowing cast alternation breaks valid vectorizations. The problem is specific to     │
│ `sext` and `zext` being incorrectly alternated.                                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ My analysis of the code revealed that the `CastInst` handling logic in `getSameOpcode` is missing a crucial check that is present in the `BinaryOperator` handling logic. The `CastInst` │
│ path enters a block with an assertion without first checking if the alternation is valid via `isValidForAlternation`. This is the root cause of the assertion failures I've been seeing. │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The correct solution requires two changes:                                                                                                                                               │
│ 1.  Make `isValidForAlternation` more precise by having it return `false` for `SExt` and `ZExt` opcodes, as these are not safe to alternate.                                             │
│ 2.  Add the missing `isValidForAlternation` checks to the `if` condition that guards the alternation logic for `CastInst`. This will prevent the assertion from being triggered for      │
│ `sext`/`zext` and will correctly allow other valid cast alternations to proceed.                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ First, I will revert my previous incorrect change to get the file back to a clean state.                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '/return InstructionsState(IBase, nullptr, nullptr);/d' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                                                           │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
